The paper discusses open-ended evolution, which is a topic commonly studied in the field of computational neuroscience and artificial intelligence (cs.NE, cs.AI). The proposed method of facilitating the formation of higher-order entities is also relevant to the field of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of a hash function as a fitness evaluator suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the simulation results and analysis of evolutionary behaviors suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
